race.comment: LET'S FLY (1) is desperate for a change of luck and she should get the right conditions in this weaker contest. Loomed strongly in the testing conditions when a fighting third to Brave Call over 2000m at Kembla Grange in BM78 class. Braith Nock retains the ride and should prove too good for these. OAKFIELD WALLABY (2) has come back in good order this time in and a win looks imminent. Caught the eye through the line when a solid fourth over 1900m at this track. Should get the right tempo and looks well placed to break through. HAPPINESS (7) lightly raced gelding heading in the right direction. Was six weeks between runs when coming from off the speed for a close-up second over 1900m at this track. Fitter now and represents good each-way value. GENERAL SOHO (6) tough old gelding with his hoof on the till. Down in the weights and not to be overlooked.
